pageContext.description: Described and illustrated in the 'Archaeologia' Object looks like the mounting for the end of a broad strap of thick leather, but with openings to allow of thin strips in continuation of main strap to come through. Like a piece of tube closed at the ends, but with longitudinal opening 5/6mm wide all along it on one side and 3 small openings 4mm x 9mm arranged at equal distances along the opposite side.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology + Ethnology, Cambridge,Purchased by the Cambridge Antiquarian Society, April 1919,1919.b
pageContext.site: England,Cambridgeshire,Wilburton,In fen-land belonging to Mr. Oliver Claude Pell,1882
